### Day 1 end-to-end walkthrough
### Requires the VS Code "REST Client" extension (or JetBrains HTTP Client) for
### variable-chaining (@name / {{req.response.body.$.field}}). Otherwise run each
### request manually, copying ids/keys from the previous response by hand.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001

### Health check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 1. Create a session
# @name createSession
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "locale": "fr",
  "storyId": "story-1",
  "childName": "Test Child"
}

### 2. Request a presigned upload URL
# @name uploadUrl
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions/{{createSession.response.body.$.sessionId}}/upload-url
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "contentType": "image/jpeg"
}

### 3. PUT the actual file to R2 — run manually (not chainable in this format), e.g.:
# curl.exe -X PUT "<uploadUrl from step 2 response>" -H "Content-Type: image/jpeg" --data-binary "@./assets/test-photos/sample.jpg"

### 4. Confirm the upload
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions/{{createSession.response.body.$.sessionId}}/upload-confirm
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "objectKey": "{{uploadUrl.response.body.$.objectKey}}"
}

### 5. Inspect the session (convenience endpoint, not in the original API spec —
### added for QA so pipeline state is visible without querying the DB directly)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/sessions/{{createSession.response.body.$.sessionId}}
